This is a modified version of the Iris Coq development to support the
submission

	Robust and Compositional Verification of Object Capability
	Patterns

See ./Iris_README.md for compilation instructions. We've tested the
development under Coq 8.6 (January 2017) and ssreflect 1.6.1, as well
as a few earlier versions.

To develop OCPL, we changed Iris' sample program logic to support
non-progressive weakeast preconditions and Iris' sample heap language
to support robust safety.

Our work on progress bits appears in ./theories/program_logic/; in
particular ./theories/program_logic/weakestpre.v.

Our work on the heap language appears in ./theories/heap_lang/. The
most interesting bits are:

	theories/heap_lang/lang.v
		language definition

	theories/heap_lang/on_val.v
		the predicate transformer called `lift` in the paper

	theories/heap_lang/heap.v
		heap resources and the invariant enforcing robust safety

	theories/heap_lang/substitution.v
	theories/heap_lang/robust_safety.v
		the proof of "internal" robust safety

	theories/heap_lang/adequacy.v
		metatheory, including the robust safety theorem stated
		in the paper

As far as examples go, you will find general object capability
patterns (OCPs) in

	./theories/heap_lang/lib/sealing.v
	./theories/heap_lang/lib/caretaker.v
	./theories/heap_lang/lib/membrane.v

and derived OCPs and client programs in

	./theories/tests/sealing.v
	./theories/tests/caretaker.v
	./theories/tests/membrane.v

(These are the files in which we apply the robust safety theorem to
whole programs.)

The paper mentions a few libraries:

	./theories/heap_lang/lib/lock.v
		./theories/heap_lang/lib/spin_lock.v
	./theories/heap_lang/lib/maps.v
